4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT ESTABLISHING THE SCHOOL MENTAL HEALTH PROMOTION
5 PILOT PROGRAM; PROVIDING THAT THE OFFICE OF PUBLIC INSTRUCTION ADMINISTER THE
6 PROGRAM; ESTABLISHING PROGRAM PARAMETERS; PROVIDING A DEFINITION; ESTABLISHING
7 REPORTING REQUIREMENTS; PROVIDING AN APPROPRIATION; PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE;
8 AND PROVIDING A TERMINATION DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 1. School mental health promotion pilot program. (1) There is a school
13 mental health promotion pilot program administered by the office of public instruction. The purpose of the
14 program is to encourage and support schools in implementing innovative, student-led, and locally determined
15 mental health promotion initiatives.
16 (2) The office of public instruction shall solicit applications from school districts seeking to
17 participate in the program and award grants to applicants displaying:
18 (a) a specific need to address mental health concerns among students of one or more schools of
19 the district;
20 (b) that the application was developed and supported by:
21 (i) students;
22 (ii) parents;
23 (iii) certified and classified staff, administrators, and trustees of the school district; and
24 (iv) community members and organizations;
25 (c) an identification of and commitment to implement specific mental health promotion activities;
26 (d) plans to develop a program management team, including representatives from the groups
27 listed under subsection (2)(b); and
28 (e) plans to evaluate the effectiveness of the program using specific metrics and establishing a
