1 peers and teachers;
2 (c) programs to increase parent and family involvement;
3 (d) intergenerational programs, such as foster grandparent programs or programs involving tribal
4 elders;
5 (e) reducing barriers to student access to individual or group counseling;
6 (f) implementing schoolwide initiatives, especially initiatives recommended for elementary and
7 secondary schools by the Montana suicide review team established in section 3, Chapter 353, Laws of 2013;
8 (g) peer mentoring programs and mentor programs utilizing community members;
9 (h) the use of creative arts and play;
10 (i) service learning and other community-based projects; and
11 (j) partnerships with youth development and empowerment organizations.
12
13 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Appropriation. (1) There is appropriated $250,000 from the general fund
14 to the office of public instruction in each year of the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, to be used for the
15 distribution of grants under [section 1].
16 (2) The legislature intends that the appropriation in this section be considered part of the ongoing
17 base for the next legislative session.
18
19 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Notification to tribal governments. The secretary of state shall send a
20 copy of [this act] to each federally recognized tribal government in Montana.
21
22 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
23 integral part of Title 20, chapter 7, part 13, and the provisions of Title 20, chapter 7, part 13, apply to [section 1].
24
25 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
26
27 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Termination. [Section 1] terminates June 30, 2029.
